  "title": "COMMISSIONING MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></u><br />Process Owner for Corporate Commissioning Process with responsibility for review, generation and updating of corporate commissioning procedures and guidelines.</p><p>Responsible for commissioning related inputs into Capex generation for projects under bid. Responsible for supporting commissioning processes of the projects under execution.</p><p>Attend vessel inspections to support Company’s bid requirements or S&P activities. Perform duties as required by the Head of Projects. Upon assuming role of a Project Commissioning Manager: -<br />Responsible for overall supervision, management and control of commissioning activities on the project. Identification and deployment of resources required for commissioning in consultation with project manager.</p><p>Responsible for identification and development of commissioning system and sub-system boundaries, management & control of completion dossiers.</p><p>Liaise with project quality team for management of mechanical completion activities and sign off acceptance dossiers following mechanical completion. Coordinate and interface with all other parties involved in commissioning like Client personnel /Operation team, vendors, shipyards etc. Liaise with operation/client for system walk through and system completion certification for handover.<br /></p><p><u><strong>QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENT</strong></u><br />Degree in Engineering, preferably in process or marine disciplines<br /></p><p><u><strong>EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENT</strong></u><br />5-10 years of experience in Commissioning of o</p>",
